{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## What\nRead-only derivations over the durable ticket event store (including compaction-retired `.retired` events) for the agent-process metrics that have a **clean, verifiable event signature today**: attempts-per-ticket, first-pass verification rate, rework at 7/30 days, reopen-recovery, and revert-linked recovery. Metrics whose signal has no reliable event vocabulary yet (escalation, cross-agent handoff/handoff-failure) are explicitly **out of scope for this ticket** and report `Unavailable` from the registry until a later ticket adds their instrumentation вҖ” this ticket does not claim them.\n\n## Data-access ground truth (the plan is built on this, not on `reduce_ticket`)\n`reduce_ticket(..., include_retired=True)` returns a **single collapsed terminal-state dict, NOT an ordered event sequence** (`src/rebar/reducer/_api.py:127`). There is **no** public ordered-event API. So the reader scans the raw event files directly: resolve the ticket dir via `rebar._engine_support.resolver.resolve_ticket_dir_name(id, tracker)` + `rebar.config.tracker_dir(repo_root)`, `os.listdir`, filter by `-<EVENT_TYPE>.json` suffix, `sorted()` (the ns-epoch filename prefix makes lexical sort chronological), `json.load`, read `event[\"timestamp\"]` (ns int) / `event[\"event_type\"]` / `event[\"data\"]`. To include compaction-retired events, also glob `*.retired` (invert `rebar.reducer._cache.is_active_event`). `Verified -1` does **not** exist anywhere in the event schema and is not used.\n\n## Files\n- `src/rebar/metrics/event_metrics.py` вҖ” new: read-only functions taking `(repo_root, since, until)`, registered into `src/rebar/metrics/registry.py`. Each returns `None` (вҶ’ c085 `Unavailable`) when the range yields no qualifying tickets; a genuine measured zero returns `0`.\n- `tests/unit/metrics/test_event_metrics.py` вҖ” new.\n\n## Metric definitions (each from a concrete, cited signal)\n- **attempts_per_ticket** вҖ” distinct claim sessions: scan raw `*-STATUS.json`, filter to the `openвҶ’in_progress` edge (`data.current_status==\"open\" and data.status==\"in_progress\"`), collect distinct `data.session` (stamped by `_stamp_session`, `txn.py:56-76`). Compiled state keeps only the *current* `claimed_session`, so raw events are required to count multiple attempts.\n- **first_pass_rate** вҖ” fraction of closed tickets in range that were never reopened: `state[\"last_reopened_at\"]` absent (set only on a `closedвҶ’open` edge, `_processors.py:304-310`).\n- **rework_within_days(n)** for nвҲҲ{7,30} вҖ” tickets with a `closedвҶ’open` STATUS edge followed by a later `вҶ’closed` edge within n days, measured from raw STATUS `timestamp`s.\n- **reopen_recovery** вҖ” count of tickets with вүҘ1 `closedвҶ’open` STATUS edge in range (raw scan).\n- **revert_recovery** вҖ” tickets whose reduced `state[\"reverts\"]` (records `{target_event_uuid, target_event_type, timestamp, ...}`, `_processors.py:452-462`) contains a revert of a `STATUS` or `COMMITS` target within range вҖ” i.e. a substantive revert, not a revert of a COMMENT/LINK.\n\n## Approach\nEverything is structurally witnessed and read-only вҖ” no new emission. HLC filename timestamps are real wall-clock ns, so date-range bucketing is exact. `source=\"structural\"`, `confidence=\"high\"` (authoritative). Compaction-retired events are included so history survives compaction.\n\n## Tests\n- Unit (real temp store; craft raw event files directly with known timestamps/sessions): a ticket with two distinct `openвҶ’in_progress` sessions yields `attempts_per_ticket==2`; a `closedвҶ’openвҶ’closed` 3 days apart counts in `rework_within_days(7)` but not a 10-day gap; a ticket closed and never reopened counts toward `first_pass_rate`; a ticket with a REVERT of a STATUS event is counted by `revert_recovery` while a ticket with only a COMMENT-revert is not; retired (`*.retired`) events are still counted.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `tests/unit/metrics/test_event_metrics.py` passes: a fixture ticket claimed by two distinct sessions yields `attempts_per_ticket == 2` (exact), and a single-session ticket yields `1`.\n- [ ] a `closedвҶ’openвҶ’closed` transition 3 days apart is counted in `rework_within_days(7)` and NOT in a variant 10 days apart вҖ” both asserted.\n- [ ] `revert_recovery` counts a ticket whose `reverts` targets a STATUS event and does NOT count one whose only revert targets a COMMENT вҖ” asserted (proves the target_event_type filter).\n- [ ] a metric over an empty range returns `None` so `evaluate()` reports `Unavailable`; a populated range with zero qualifying events returns `0` (measured zero) вҖ” both asserted.\n- [ ] the metrics register into `src/rebar/metrics/registry.py` with `source=\"structural\"` and are authoritative вҖ” asserted."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784439553006698001,"uuid":"413bffb0-0c74-4993-bbfd-18c97a51b524"}